iew-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1062%2C709 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1416%2C945 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=403%2C269, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=807%2C539 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1212%2C809 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=403%2C269, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=807%2C539 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1212%2C809 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 589px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=553%2C369, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1106%2C738 2x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(max-width: 589px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=553%2C369, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1106%2C738 2x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1237%2C826 2x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1237%2C826 2x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=406%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=813%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1221%2C815 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=406%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=813%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1221%2C815 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=554%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1109%2C740 2x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=554%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1109%2C740 2x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"Winter training\" title=\"Winter training\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2019/12/cp-shortest-day_324_preview-94b5636.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=619%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> Winter on the bike can be tough. Follow our tips to get the most out of the season.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Andy McCandlish/Immediate Media</i></span></p></div><h2>Not eating properly post-ride</h2><p><span>Riding your bike over the winter months can be a great way of keeping trim.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>But while it’s tempting to dive into a selection box as soon as you finish your ride, it’s important to refuel your body properly to start the recovery process.</span></p><p><span>“It’s key to replenish your glycogen stores,” says Bottrill. “Once you’ve finished your training, remember to take in your protein and carbohydrates.”</span></p><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/the-basics-of-recovery-explained/\">The basics of recovery explained</a></li></ul><h2>Not recovering between interval sessions</h2><p><span>If you’ve got less than an hour for a training session, then a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/hiit-interval-training/\">HIIT workout</a> – where you intersperse short, high-intensity intervals with short periods of recovery – is a time-efficient way of keeping your fitness up over winter.</span></p><p><span>But it’s also important to factor in recovery time between sessions, due to their intensity and what they take out of the body.</span></p><p><span>”If you’re doing that day-in-day-out, you’re going to burn out really quickly,” says Bottrill. “If you have 30-40 minutes of training time, there’s a benefit, but you can’t do it every day. It’s not feasibly possible because you can’t hit that high intensity.”</span></p><h2>Overdoing it</h2><p><span>Although it might be tempting to try and get a real leg-up ahead of next season, it is possible to burn out before you’ve even got there. “We call them winter warriors,” says Bottrill.</span></p><p><span>Instead, he recommends setting goals and working out a structured plan that will help you achieve those objectives, without burning out and suffering from <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/fitness-and-training/overtraining-syndrome/\">overtraining</a>.</span></p><p><span>After all, you want to get to spring ready to take your training to that next level, rather than arrive at your peak.</span></p></section></div>","author":"Charlie Allenby","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"398fb68384179db36a9d104d8626478bb22390c1670603db24c94d055659af2d","category":"Cycling"}